article.headline: Jackson St. 87, Ark.-Pine Bluff 83
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. -- Garrison Johnson scored 16 of his 23 points in the second half and Jackson State rallied to beat Arkansas-Pine Bluff 87-83 on Monday night. The Tigers (8-13, 7-2 Southwestern Athletic Conference) trailed 46-41 at halftime before shooting 64.7 percent from the field in the second half (11 of 17), behind Johnson and 12 points from Darrion Griffin. The Tigers, having not led since 13:36 left in the first half, took their final lead with 10:17 left to play on four consecutive free throws. Johnson was fouled by Tavaris Washington, and then the Golden Lions (7-13, 6-3) were called for a technical foul. Four free throws later, Jackson State had a 61-57 lead. Jeremy Caldwell added 20 points and Griffin finished with 18 for the Tigers. The Golden Lions were paced by Terrance Calvin with 26 points and Washington with 15.
